title: Volleyball: GHS makes history, claims first region crown
text:
Gainesville volleyball players react to winning the Region 8- crown on Saturday in Bethlehem. Related Articles Volleyball: Lady Vikings claim second straight 7-AAA crown Volleyball: Gainesville opens 8- tourney with win Volleyball: Jefferson clinches state berth with win over E. Jackson Volleyball: North Hall finishes with No. 3 seed from 8-AAAA 
BETHLEHEM — The Gainesville volleyball team made history on Saturday, claiming the program's first region title. 
The Lady Red Elephants (35-11) defeated Clarke-Central (25-19, 25-22), Lanier (25-8, 25-18) and Lanier again in the Region 8- championship match 3-1 (25-18, 20-25, 25-18, 25-15). 
All players contributed to the Red Elephants success. Sydney King (named first team Region 8- Libero) recorded 5 assists, and 38 digs. Caroline Mercer added 12 digs. Morgan Frazier pitched in 1 dig and 1 kill. Tangi Miller had 3 digs, 3 blocks, and 6 kills. Bessie Winston added 4 digs and 10 kills. Sally Callahan had 1 ace and 10 digs. Tanai Watson (2nd Team 8- Outside Hitter) added 22 digs and 25 kills. Cori Griffith had 2 digs, 2 blocks, and 16 kills. Abby Alexander (second Team 8- Middle Hitter) added 6 blocks and 9 kills. Anna Wylie had 4 aces, 10 digs, 6 blocks, and 4 kills. Savannah Roys (first team 8- Setter) had 4 aces, 69 assists, and 31 digs. Ashley Filson added 1 ace and 1 dig. Emily Sloan had 8 digs. Ayanna Griffith had 1 kill. 
Gainesville's Randi Moore was named Coach of the Year for 8- . 
The Lady Red Elephants will play host to Alexander, the No. 4 seed out of Region 5- , on Thursday in the first round of the state playoffs. Associated Tags : High school volleyball, Gainesville volleyball © Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
